  "identifier": "crew",
  "description": "The 'R6' classes of 'crew' establish a standardized user interface to high-performance computing technologies. Unlike the closely related 'future' package (2021, <doi:10.32614/RJ-2021-048>), 'crew' prioritizes centralized scheduling, heterogeneous semi-persistent workers, and user-driven customization. The purpose is to enable pipeline tools such as such 'targets' (2021, <doi:10.21105/joss.02959>) to efficiently orchestrate tasks without having to support individual low-level interfaces to specific high-performance computing platforms or cloud services.",
